<h2>GoogleVisualr - Map</h2>
<div class='append-bottom'>
  <hr>
  <h3>Overview</h3>
  <p>
    Displays a map using the Google Maps API with data values (coordinates or addresses) being displayed as points on the map.
  </p>
  <p>
    Please refer to <%= link_to "Google's documentation", "http://code.google.com/apis/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/map.html" %> for details on <em>Data Format</em> and <em>Configuration Options</em>. However, <em>Methods</em> and <em>Events</em> are not implemented.
  </p>
  <p>
    Important: Please specify the height and width of the div element explicitly.
  </p>
</div>
<div class='append-bottom'>
  <hr>
  <h3>Example</h3>
  <div id='chart' style='width: 400px; height: 300px'></div>
  <%= render_chart @chart, 'chart' %>
</div>
<div class='append-bottom'>
  <hr>
  <h3>Code</h3>
  <div>
    <p>
      In your controller, create the data_table object, set new columns, add row values, then instantiate the chart with configuration options.
    </p>
    <script src="https://gist.github.com/1057959.js?file=controller.rb"></script>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      In your view, use the <em>to_js</em> method to generate <%= link_to "JavaScript", "http://code.google.com/apis/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/map.html#Example" %>, during rendering of the view.
    </p>
    <script src="https://gist.github.com/1057959.js?file=view.html.erb"></script>
  </div>
</div>